# SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-only
# Project: AstraDesk
# File: .trivyignore
#
# Supply-chain accepted-risk allow-list for the fail-closed image scan gate
# (GitHub issue #40 — NEW-01 dependency & supply-chain remediation).
#
# scripts/ci/supply_chain_scan.sh passes this file to `trivy image
# --ignorefile`. Every active entry below is a disposition under INV-SC-1
# (docs/roadmap/issues/ISSUES_NEW-01_supply_chain.md): it MUST be either
#   (a) a documented false positive (the scanner is wrong: the flagged code
#       path is not present, or the version match is incorrect), or
#   (b) a proven non-reachable finding (the vulnerable code is present in
#       the image but no execution path reaches it), justified in a comment
#       immediately above the entry.
#
# This file must NOT be used to defer a reachable HIGH/CRITICAL finding that
# is merely inconvenient to fix yet (INV-SC-2). Reachable findings must be
# remediated (dependency bump, resolver-safe pin) or the build must fail.
#
# Format (one advisory ID per line, optional expiry):
#   CVE-2024-12345
#   GHSA-xxxx-yyyy-zzzz exp:2026-12-31
#
# INV-SC-4: every entry with an `exp:` date must be re-justified or removed
# before it expires; Trivy re-fails the gate once the date passes. Entries
# without an `exp:` date are not permitted — every acceptance here is
# time-boxed by contract.
#
# `starlette`/`fastapi` and `transformers` were previously listed here as
# pending Python-package findings and are now fully remediated (see
# audit/evidence/40_dependency_triage.md's follow-up sections) — zero
# Python-package HIGH/CRITICAL findings remain in `astradesk:ci-python-scoped`.
#
# The entries below are the last remaining findings in that image: Debian
# trixie (13) OS packages with no upstream fixed version published on any
# current Debian suite at the time of this pass (confirmed via each
# advisory's Trivy `Status` field: `affected` or `fix_deferred`, and
# `FixedVersion` empty in `audit/evidence/40_trivy_api_gateway_scoped.json`).
# The pinned base image digest (`python@sha256:eb43ff12...` in `Dockerfile`)
# was re-confirmed via `docker buildx imagetools inspect python:3.13-slim`
# to already be the latest published manifest for that tag — there is no
# newer digest to refresh to. Full disposition table:
# audit/evidence/40_dependency_triage.md ("Debian OS accepted-risk" table).
#
# Each entry is time-boxed to exp:2026-08-31 per INV-SC-4 — this forces
# re-review (renew, remove, or replace with a real fix) at the next
# hardening window rather than becoming a silent permanent exception.
# scripts/ci/supply_chain_scan.sh validates at scan time that every active
# entry below carries a non-expired `exp:` date; Trivy itself (confirmed
# v0.72.0) also stops suppressing a finding once its `exp:` date passes.

# gzip 1.13-1 (Debian trixie) — global buffer overflow in LZH decompression.
# Trivy Status: affected, no FixedVersion.
CVE-2026-41992 exp:2026-08-31

# libacl1 2.3.2-2+b1 (Debian trixie) — symlink traversal privilege escalation.
# Trivy Status: affected, no FixedVersion.
CVE-2026-54369 exp:2026-08-31

# libncursesw6/libtinfo6/ncurses-base/ncurses-bin 6.5+20250216-2 (Debian
# trixie) — one CVE ID spans all four scanned packages from the ncurses
# source package. Buffer overflow, possible arbitrary code execution.
# Trivy Status: affected, no FixedVersion.
CVE-2025-69720 exp:2026-08-31

# perl-base 5.40.1-6 (Debian trixie) — 5 distinct advisories against the
# bundled perl-Archive-Tar/perl-IO-Compress/perl-base modules. Trivy Status:
# affected or fix_deferred (Debian Security Tracker: no patched perl-base
# published for any current suite at any of these IDs), no FixedVersion.
CVE-2026-42496 exp:2026-08-31
CVE-2026-8376 exp:2026-08-31
CVE-2026-42497 exp:2026-08-31
CVE-2026-48962 exp:2026-08-31
CVE-2026-9538 exp:2026-08-31
